Quick Overview:
1/4" x 12" HSS Aircraft Extension Drill Bit

  • Ideal for drilling in mild steel where extra length for reach is required
  • 135 degree split point for self-centering and reduces thrust
  • Black oxide surface treatment that is abrasion resistant, reduces chip welding and improves chip flow
  • Manufactured to Aerospace Standard 907
  • Sizes smaller than 1/16 and #52 have the 118 degree standard point

While we are happy to sell this product in any quantity you desire, we prefer this item be purchased in multiples of 12 in order to not break product packaging.

Quick Overview:
7/32" HSS 2 Flute Single End End Mill

  • Used for general-purpose milling including profiling, slotting, roughing, cutting keyways and pockets
  • These versatile end mills can be used on a wide range of materials such as aluminum, steel, and stainless steel
  • Their large core diameter provides rigidity and reduces deflection while the cutting geometry allows for rapid stock removal
  • End Mills come in a wide range of styles including single end, double end, center cutting, corner rounding and roughing
  • Available in varied lengths, flutes and shapes such as square end and ball nose

Quick Overview:
#24 HSS Black & Gold KFD Split Point Jobber Length Drill Bit.

  • KFD Killer Force Drill Bits are manufactured from M2 premium grade high speed steel.
  • For use in a wide range of materials in the iron and steel families such aluminum, iron, stainless steel and other hard metal drilling.
  • 135 degree split point tip for self-centering and reducing thrust. Compared to a conventional 118 degree tip, these drills wont go "walking" on you.
  • Black and gold surface treated for use in stainless steel and other hard metal drilling

Quick Overview:
3/8" x 4" Carbide Tipped Masonry Drill Bit

  • Designed for drilling in brick, concrete and sandstone
  • Carbide tipped round shank masonry drills are engineered with wide fultes to provide fast dust removal in softer materials
  • Carbide tips brazed to tough steel bodies and are larger than the nominal drill size to provide clearance for installation of anchor screws, expansion shields and toggle bolts
  • Designed for use in portable electric drills.
